Overview
This project applies unsupervised learning techniques to identify underlying flood event regimes using hydrologic and meteorological data. The goal is to improve parametric flood insurance trigger design by diagnosing where current triggers fail.

We use:
Principal Component Analysis (PCA)
Kernel PCA (k-PCA)
Clustering (K-means)
Density-based clustering (DBSCAN)
Anomaly detection

Objectives
Identify distinct flood regimes (fluvial, pluvial, mixed)
Detect extreme and anomalous flood events
Evaluate how well current triggers capture different regimes
Use results to inform improved parametric trigger design

Files 
raw file --> combined_data_1975_2025_all.csv
cleaned file --> daily_with_flow_percentile.csv
feature engineering --> event_level_features.csv (use this for analysis)
standardized --> event_level_features_modeling_only.csv (use this for eval)

